HEADWORD: Hispid
<hw>His"pid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>hispidus</ets>: cf. F. <ets>hispide</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Rough with bristles or minute spines.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot. & Zool.)</fld> <def>Beset with stiff hairs or
bristles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hispidulous</ent>⟦br⟧
